This paper discusses privacy protection in Location-Based Services (LBSs) through decentralization. The primary focus is on the security and privacy aspects of LBSs, which falls under the category of "Computer Science and Security" (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the use of distributed systems and algorithms to achieve privacy protection, which falls under the categories of "Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing" (cs.DC) and "Data Structures and Algorithms" (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of resilient systems to ensure privacy protection, which falls under the category of "Social and Information Networks" (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed system, which falls under the category of "Software Engineering" (cs.SE).
